[B]I think I had my best rez experience on my druid, hehe.  I was 33 at the time, and I had LITERALLY lost 33 more times than I have levels on her.  Different things happened... zoned to WC, just in time to get stomped by a nightfall giant right as sow ran.  Zoned into NK right on top of grimfeather.  Ported someone to SFG, ran outside, found out I was KOS to the Qeynos guards (still dont' know why, but fixed the faction with bandits).  Had someone PULL, yes PULL an ice giant to our group in everfrost.  Speaking of Everfrost, can you say martar icebear?  Oh, and don't forget and wolf form yourself there, either.  Etc, etc.  

Anyhow, I finally got a whole yellow into 33!  Enough to cushion me, right?  Well, I then got trained, and chain killed on my bind point.  By this time, I was in tears.  I had carefully scrimped and saved 100pp, so I offered it in the next zone over where high levels hang out.  I figured no one would do it, as 100 wasn't much for the number of rezes I needed and they were all almost for sure grouped, anyhow.

Well, a paladin came out, rezed ALL those corpses, and then logged while I was trying to give him the cash.  "paladin tells you, I'm busy right now" then vanishes. It was enough to reding me.  I was at that point willing to take any rez, LOL, just so long as it dinged me, and those 50% rezes did the trick for me.  I've a lot to catch up to where i was at, but at least I still have my level!  (lame, eh?  hehe)[/B][/QUOTE]

